(nL2TLBWays, nICacheTLBWays).explanation: These are independent hardware configuration parameters for different TLB structures that do not directly influence each other's design or operation;

(nL2TLBWays, CPI).explanation: Increasing L2 TLB associativity reduces TLB miss rates which decreases memory access latency and subsequently improves cycles per instruction performance;

(nL2TLBWays, nICacheWays).explanation: These are independent cache configuration parameters that operate on different levels of the memory hierarchy without direct causal influence on each other;
